{{Youmay|the [[Akivan]]|[[Ruto Graven]], an [[Assistant Minister of Internal Affairs]] on [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]}}
{{Quote|The Empire has a large operation on one of the islands in the Great Basin. My sources tell me they are looking for artifacts for 'cultural importance'. Needless to say we cannot let them take our history! A group of us are planning to sabotage the operation. Whatever the consequences. Are you in? Now delete this message. I mean that Ruto!|Data message to Ruto|<ref name="Outlaws" />}}
'''Ruto''' was an individual who resided on the [[Outer Rim Territories|Outer Rim]] [[jungle]] [[planet]] [[Akiva]] during the [[Imperial Era|reign]] of the [[Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Outlaws">''[[Star Wars Outlaws]]''</ref> 
By [[3 ABY]],<ref name="OutlawsDate">{{OutlawsDate}}</ref> Ruto had been sent a message by a [[Unidentified Akivan rebel|fellow]] [[Akivan]] who had learned that the Empire had established an [[Excavation Site 12|excavation site]] in the [[Great Basin]] region of Akiva to search for artifacts for cultural importance. In the message, the Akivan expressed their belief that the Empire's operation would result in the [[thief|theft]] of Akivan history and went on to share their plan to sabotage the site. They concluded the message by asking Ruto to join them as well as reminding Ruto to delete the message. The communication ultimately end up in possession of the Empire, a copy of it was stored on a [[datapad]] at the excavation site<ref name="Outlaws" /> in 3 [['ABY-BBY' dating system|ABY]].<ref name="OutlawsDate" />

{{Gamemechanics|Star Wars Outlaws|canon=1}}
That [[Standard year|year]],<ref name="OutlawsDate" /> the thief [[Kay Vess]] found and read the datapad while at the excavation site.<ref name="Outlaws" />
{{Endgame}}

==Behind the scenes==
Ruto was mentioned in the [[2024]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]], ''[[Star Wars Outlaws]]'' developed by [[Massive Entertainment]] and published by [[Ubisoft]]. The datapad entry mentioning Ruto was not part of any of the game's quests and did not impact the game's story.<ref name="Outlaws" />

